---

<section
  class="relative w-full text-zinc-100 border-t border-zinc-800/50 bg-gradient-to-b from-zinc-950/90 to-zinc-950/40"
  aria-labelledby="about-title"
>
  <div
    class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 sm:py-20 md:py-28 flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-12 lg:gap-16 lg:items-start"
  >
    <div
      class="shrink-0 w-full max-w-sm lg:max-w-[12rem] lg:pt-1"
    >
      <p
        class="text-[0.7rem] sm:text-xs font-medium tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-[#e9552f]/85"
      >
        Philosophy
      </p>
      <h2
        id="about-title"
        class="eurostile mt-3 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight"
      >
        How I work
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div
      class="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-6 sm:space-y-7 text-sm sm:text-base text-zinc-400 font-light leading-[1.75] max-w-2xl"
    >
      <p id="about-first-text">
        Performance is a product feature. I treat web vitals, bundle shape, and
        data-fetching as design constraints—because they decide whether a
        feature feels “premium” in production, not in a local demo. That mindset
        scales to teams: shared foundations beat one-off heroics.
      </p>
      <p id="about-second-text">
        Platform work is how frontend seniority compounds: design systems,
        build pipelines, and clear boundaries between product surfaces. I
        invest there so the next project ships faster with fewer regressions,
        and so engineers can reason about the system a year from now.
      </p>
      <p id="about-third-text">
        I work best in cross-functional teams with strong product
        ownership—where tradeoffs are explicit, written down, and tied to
        business outcomes, not just ticket throughput.
      </p>
      <p class="pt-2">
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 border-b border-zinc-600 border-dotted hover:text-[#e9552f]/90 hover:border-[#e9552f]/40 transition-colors"
        >
          Extended background
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script type="text/javascript">
  const userLang = navigator.language || navigator.userLanguage;
  const isEn = userLang.includes("en");
  const enTitle = "How I work";
  const esTitle = "Cómo trabajo";

  const enFirst = `Performance is a product feature. I treat web vitals, bundle shape, and
        data-fetching as design constraints—because they decide whether a
        feature feels “premium” in production, not in a local demo. That mindset
        scales to teams: shared foundations beat one-off heroics.`;
  const esFirst = `El rendimiento es parte del producto. Trato los Web Vitals, el bundle y
        el fetching de datos como restricciones de diseño, porque definen si
        una funcionalidad se siente sólida en producción, no en un entorno
        local. Esa lógica escala al equipo: bases compartidas superan
        hazañas aisladas.`;

  const enSecond = `Platform work is how frontend seniority compounds: design systems,
        build pipelines, and clear boundaries between product surfaces. I
        invest there so the next project ships faster with fewer regressions,
        and so engineers can reason about the system a year from now.`;
  const esSecond = `La plataforma es donde se multiplica el impacto: sistemas de diseño,
        pipelines de build y límites claros entre superficies. Ese esfuerzo
        acelera el siguiente producto, reduce regresiones y mantiene el
        sistema entendible al año.`;

  const enThird = `I work best in cross-functional teams with strong product
        ownership—where tradeoffs are explicit, written down, and tied to
        business outcomes, not just ticket throughput.`;
  const esThird = `Me integro mejor con equipos multidisciplinares y con ownership
        de producto: tradeoffs explícitos, documentados, alineados al negocio
        y no solo al flujo de tareas.`;

  const aboutTitle = document.getElementById("about-title");
  const p1 = document.getElementById("about-first-text");
  const p2 = document.getElementById("about-second-text");
  const p3 = document.getElementById("about-third-text");
  if (aboutTitle && p1 && p2 && p3) {
    if (!isEn) {
      aboutTitle.innerText = esTitle;
      p1.innerText = esFirst.replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim();
      p2.innerText = esSecond.replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim();
      p3.innerText = esThird.replace(/\s+/g, " ").trim();
    }
  }
</script>
